# Solicitation Analysis Report: 70CMSW26I00000001

---

## Solicitation Summary

**Title:** Boxed Meals at Broadview IL  
**Solicitation Number:** 70CMSW26I00000001  
**Agency:** US Department of Homeland Security (ICE)  
**Location:** ICE Detention Facility, Broadview, Illinois  
**Posted:** November 7, 2025  
**Proposal Deadline:** November 11, 2025 at 12:00 PM ET  
**Period of Performance:** Three (3) months from award; possible extension  
**Link:** [SAM.gov Solicitation](https://sam.gov/workspace/contract/opp/2c07aa2cdd6841e781b26767aac1fdcf/view)

---

## Scope & Key Requirements

- Prepare, package, and deliver 70 boxed meals per meal (breakfast, lunch, dinner; 210 total/day) at the specified facility.
- All meals must meet USDA RDA nutrition guidelines.
    - **Breakfast:** protein, whole grains, fruit, dairy
    - **Lunch & Dinner:** protein entrée, whole grains, vegetables, fruit, beverage
- Menu must include options for vegetarian, low-sodium, gluten-free, nut-free, and other dietary restrictions.
- Meals must be individually packaged in eco-friendly containers and clearly labeled.
- Meals must be prepared in a licensed, inspected kitchen by food-safety-trained staff.
- Delivery in temperature-controlled vehicles; drop-offs at 6:00 AM, 12:00 PM, and 6:00 PM daily.
- Weekly menu plan submission/approval; government approval required for substitutions.
- Recordkeeping for prep, delivery, compliance is required.
- All delivery personnel must pass background checks and follow facility security protocols.
- Maintain a quality assurance plan; government may inspect at any time.
- Immediate reporting of any delivery/quality issues to government contact.

